<section
  class="relative w-full flex justify-center overflow-hidden z-10"
  aria-labelledby="about-heading"
>
  <div class="relative w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-15 py-6 sm:py-8 flex flex-col gap-2 z-10">
    
    <!-- About Heading -->
    <h1
      id="about-heading"
      class="text-[50px] [font-family:'GeistPixelSquare'] text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"
      data-aos="focus-up"
    >
      about
    </h1>

    <!-- About Content -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-8 max-w-4xl" data-aos="focus-up" data-aos-delay="100">
      <p class="text-base text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 font-product-sans leading-relaxed">
        My design and coding journey started back in 8th grade, when I accidentally fell in love with graphic design and web development and never recovered. Fast forward to 2023: I got into <strong>FAST NU</strong> for <strong>Computer Science</strong>, started freelancing, and began networking like a pro on LinkedIn and through societies. That's when I teamed up with a senior who launched a design agency called <strong>Pixen</strong>. Now I work part-time as a <strong>UI/UX Designer</strong> and <strong>Frontend Developer</strong>, helping build <strong>20+ SaaS landing pages</strong>, <strong>web apps</strong>, and <strong>3+ mobile apps</strong>.
      </p>

      <p class="text-base text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 font-product-sans leading-relaxed">
        I've also been an active <strong>Hacktoberfest</strong> contributor since 2023 (yes, I keep coming back for more). I love building things that actually work and look good doing it. Curious? Check out my projects to see what I've been up to!
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
